        <bioghist id="ref1">
            <head>Biographical Note</head>
            <p>James Hurst, a native of Andover, Connecticut enlisted in the Army Air Force on March 27, 1943 at the age of seventeen. James began his military career as a Pilot Cadet his first step towards achieving his dream of becoming a United States Air Force pilot. During World War II James was trained to fly both B-25 and B-24 bombers among other aircraft. He served as a member of the 782nd Bomb Squadron and the 465th Bomb Group and attained the rank of 1st Lieutenant. James Hurst earned four Air Medals and the Distinguished Flying Cross.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent id="ref2">
            <head>Scope Note</head>
            <p>This collection details James Hurst’s experiences and training during his enlistment in World War II as well as the years following. A taped interview was conducted on February 16, 2004 at James’ home by Eileen Hurst. The collection consists of the taped interview and reproductions of photographs. The materials cover James’ experiences from 1943 thru 1945, providing evidence of American troop combat activity, American flight training and deployment, and U.S. military moral and courage under fire.</p>
        </scopecontent>
